This article is a press release from the White House Office of the Press Secretary. It is a statement made by the President after a meeting with cabinet members to discuss the Deepwater Horizon oil spill. The President discussed the progress in capturing the oil and the need for BP to be accountable for the economic impact on local businesses. He also emphasized the importance of protecting the health of workers involved in the cleanup and monitoring the impact on the general population and the environment. The President mentioned the need for transparency and scientific analysis of the situation. He concluded by expressing confidence in overcoming the crisis and using it as an opportunity to improve the livelihood and quality of life in the affected region.